You are using the common tactic of forcing someone to disprove a negative.  There is no "if-then" argument required for something which has absolutely no evidence.  According to your reasoning I am justified in inventing anything that pops into my head and it is incumbent upon you to disprove it.  This is not science.P.S. - Characterizing atheists as "passionate" is like calling a rationalist "emotional".  